      "content": "that mud analogy makes sense, but i'm still trying to wrap my head around the \"fighting back\" part. it sounds like the inductor is almost actively working against the voltage to prevent the current from changing. is there a better way to describe that kind of behavior? like, is there a specific term for when something resists change in a system like that?",
